    public static enum NorwegianIdNumber.Type
extends Enum<NorwegianIdNumber.Type>
    Describes the type of the given Norwegian ID.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DNUMBER
      A D-number is assigned to people that are living in Norway on a short term basis.
      FHNUMBER
      FH-numbers are assigned in medical context where the numbers cannot be interpreted besides their validity.
      FNUMBER
      A F-number represents a normal ID as assigned to each Norwegian citizen and to people living in Norway on a long-term basis.
      HNUMBER
      H-numbers are assigned to persons that are neither assigned a F-number or a D-number.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • FNUMBER

        public static final NorwegianIdNumber.Type FNUMBER
        A F-number represents a normal ID as assigned to each Norwegian citizen and to people living in Norway on a long-term basis.

      • DNUMBER

        public static final NorwegianIdNumber.Type DNUMBER
        A D-number is assigned to people that are living in Norway on a short term basis. Compared to F-numbers, the number 4 is added to the first digit in order to differentiate D-numbers.

      • HNUMBER

        public static final NorwegianIdNumber.Type HNUMBER
        H-numbers are assigned to persons that are neither assigned a F-number or a D-number. They are marked by adding the number 4 to the third digit in order to differentiate H-numbers.

      • FHNUMBER

        public static final NorwegianIdNumber.Type FHNUMBER
        FH-numbers are assigned in medical context where the numbers cannot be interpreted besides their validity. They are marked by an 8 or 9 as their first digit.
